verbose_text: Kong et al. [XREF_BIBR] found that the increased CTX level had the specificity and sensitivity of 65.6% and 68.8%, respectively, in the diagnosis of bone metastasis in non small cell lung cancer patients, and they speculated that CTX could be used to screen the bone metastasis of lung cancer, which was supported by Ebert et al. [XREF_BIBR].
